Billy Currington&#039;s third album, Little Bit of Everything, will be 

released on Oct. 
14 by Mercury Nashville. Currington co-produced the album with Carson 
Chamberlain and co-wrote five of the 12 songs.

"People kept asking what kind of music they&#039;d hear on this next album, 
whether it was going to be R&B, pop, country or rock, and I seemed to 

keep 
saying the same thing," said Currington. "It&#039;s going to be a little bit 

of 
everything, I guess." Currington has topped the country singles chart 

with 
"Good Directions" and "Must Be Doin&#039; Somethin&#039; Right."
